Subject: [PATCH 071/124] include: linux: heki: Quick fix for all blacklist
 hashes not being passed to...

VTL0 passes all the blacklissted hashes to VTL1 so that VTL1 is aware of
these hashes and rejects any authentication requests involving these
hashes. The number of hashes that can be passed are hardcoded. Increase
this count so that all the hashes get added for Azure Linux 3.0.  The
proper fix for this is to convert the gathering of blacklist hashes from
array to a linked list

Signed-off-by: Thara Gopinath <tgopinath@microsoft.com>

----
#### AI description  (iteration 1)
#### PR Classification
Bug fix

#### PR Summary
This pull request addresses an issue where not all blacklist hashes were being passed correctly.
- `include/linux/heki.h`: Increased `HEKI_MAX_TOTAL_HASHES` from 100 to 400 to ensure all blacklist hashes are included.
---
 include/linux/heki.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/heki.h b/include/linux/heki.h
index 8c8adbb703dd..0f2562c7c83b 100644
--- a/include/linux/heki.h
+++ b/include/linux/heki.h
@@ -158,7 +158,7 @@ struct heki_mod {
 #ifdef CONFIG_HEKI
 
 /* Currently 83 hashes get added to the blacklist keyring */
-#define HEKI_MAX_TOTAL_HASHES 100
+#define HEKI_MAX_TOTAL_HASHES 400
 
